John Woodbridge was charged with murder after his elderly wife was found dead on Monday morning in their home, Avon and Somerset Police announced. The police are investigating the elderly man after the incident.    Mr Woodbridge appeared in Bristol Magistrates' Court on Thursday, a force spokesman said. He is set to appear before Bristol Crown Court on March 17. In a statement, Avon and Somerset Police said: "A man has been charged after an investigation into the death of a woman in Weston-super-Mare.    "Anne Woodbridge, 92, was found deceased at a residential address on the morning of Monday January 30. "John Woodbridge, of Ashcombe Road, has subsequently been charged with murder. "The 91-year-old was due before Bristol Magistrates Court today (Thursday February 2)."  